User Management API 

Overview

The User Management API allows developers to retrieve and manage user profile information in an application.
Use this API to:
•	Fetch user details
•	Verify user existence
•	Integrate user data into other systems

Base URL
https://api.example.com/v1

Authentication

This API uses Bearer Token authentication.
How to authenticate
1.	Open URL: https://exam.ple.com/ in a web browser.
2.	Click Sign in. The Sign in page displays.
3.	Click Register. The register page displays.
4.	Enter required personal information.
5.	Click register.  Email will be received once registered.
Note: An email is also sent for approval. You cannot sign into the API 
Portal until registration is approved.
6.	Once approved, you will receive an approval mail.
7.	Include the token in the Authorization header.
Header format
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>

Endpoint: Get User Profile

Retrieves profile information for a specific user.
HTTP Method
GET
Endpoint URL
/users/{userId}
Path Parameters

Parameter	Type	Required	Description
userId	string	Yes	Unique identifier of the user

Request Example (curl)
curl -X GET "https://api.example.com/v1/users/12345" \
-H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"

Response Example (200 OK)
{
  "id": "12345",
  "name": "Akshit Patel",
  "email": "akshit@example.com",
  "status": "active"
}
Response Fields
Field	Type	Description
id	string	User ID
name	string	Full name of the user
email	string	Email address
status	string	Account status

Error Codes

Status Code	Meaning	Description
400	Bad Request	Invalid user ID format
401	Unauthorized	Missing or invalid token
404	Not Found	User does not exist
500	Server Error	Internal server error

List of APIs

API Name	HTTP Method	Endpoint	Description
Get User Profile	GET	/users/{userId}	Retrieves profile information for a specific user
Create User	POST	/users	Creates a new user account
Update User	PUT	/users/{userId}	Updates an existing user’s profile details
Delete User	DELETE	/users/{userId}	Permanently deletes a user account





